layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 2; ruled lines: 24 54; written lines: 24 54; Non-uniform layout. A number of leaves oversized and folded. Catchwords on every page. Initial words and headings in larger characters. Numerous marginal notes and additions. Original Hebrew folation near the end.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Italian cursive script of the 17th century. Partly written by Solomon Portaleone and Samuel Portaleone.

binding.p: BM in-house. Spine: 'Solomon Ibn Al-Kabits. Berith Hal-Levi. Etc. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27,011.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Giuseppe Almanzi (b. 1801, d. 1860), bibliophile; his manuscript no. 121: his library including 322 medieval Hebrew manuscripts were purchased en bloc by the British Museum in October 1865 for £1,000 through Asher & Co., Berlin bookseller and dealer to the British Museum: inscribed, folio [312v] (fse005v).
